===Etymology===
Named after Prince William, Duke of Clarence and St Andrews, later to become [[w:William IV of the United Kingdom|William IV of the United Kingdom]].

===Noun===
'''clarence'''

#A kind of [[carriage]] popular in the 19th century; a four-wheeled horse-driven vehicle with a glass front and room for four passengers.

